# Data files - too large for git, download separately (see SETUP_GUIDE.md).
# Exception: the three generated CSVs are committed anyway (~2.4MB total)
# because backend/Dockerfile.render (Render deploy) needs them baked into
# the image -- Render clones from GitHub, so gitignored files are simply
# absent there, unlike backend/docker-compose.yml's local bind-mount.
data/ml-100k/
data/*.csv
!data/items.csv
!data/train_positives.csv
!data/test_positives.csv

# Trained model artifacts - regenerated by running the scripts. Same
# exception as above: the files backend/recommender.py actually loads at
# runtime are committed (~4.4MB total); analysis-only outputs (EDA plot,
# results table) stay ignored since nothing at runtime needs them.
# NOTE: a bare "artifacts/" directory-ignore blocks git from ever
# descending into it to evaluate file-level negations below, so the
# directory itself must be un-ignored (!artifacts/) before re-ignoring its
# contents by default and negating the specific files we want.
artifacts/*
!artifacts/
!artifacts/two_tower.pt
!artifacts/item_vecs.npy
!artifacts/content_vecs.npy
!artifacts/content_movie_ids.npy
!artifacts/movie_meta.csv

# Secrets - never commit API keys
.env

# Backend local fallback state (used when Postgres isn't running)
backend/feedback.db
streamlit_app/*.log

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
env/

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.ipynb_checkpoints

# Frontend (Phase 3)
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
